.TH "xmonobut" 1
.SH NAME
xmonobut \- An X11 tool for changing mouse button behavior. 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xmonobut
-help
.br
.B xmonobut
[options...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Xmonobut is a simple X11 application that helps access 2nd and 3rd
mouse buttons on touchscreen / single mouse button ( such as Macs ) machines.

The 'missing' buttons are made accessible by briefly modifying the
mouses button map. This can be done by clicking on the xmonobut window
to 'rotate' the mouse buttons or xmonobut can be bound to a key, so
that holding this key and clicking will produce an alternate button click.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-display
Specify the XServer for xmonobut to connect to. Defaults to
$DISPLAY environmental variable. 
.TP
.B \-k <keycode>
keycode to grab. Tap once for right mouse button , quickly tap twice 
for middle button ( disabled if middle button keycode selected ).
.TP
.B \-t <value>   
Time in milliseconds to catch double clicks. Defaults to 200.
.TP
.B \-m <keycode> 
Keycode to grab for middle mouse button.
.TP
.B \-n           
Do not display dock window.
.TP
.B \-c           
Do not change cursor when button is changed. 
.TP
.B \-help
 Display a brief help message and exit. 
.SH MORE INFO
Visit http://www.handhelds.org/~mallum/matchbox/
.SH "SEE ALSO"
X(7)
.SH BUGS
If xmonobut is bound to a key, releasing the mouse button before the
bound key may cause unpredictable results.

If you find others, please report to mallum@handhelds.org.

